OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGreater Manchester PC      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'knowingly took advantage' 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fof woman                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A PC who "took advantage" of a woman he
OL,6, "knew to be vulnerable" has been found 
OL,7, guilty of misconduct in public office. 
OL,9,FThe Independent Office for Police      
OL,10,FConduct (IOPC) found Simon Rose had an 
OL,11,F"inappropriate" relationship with the  
OL,12,Fwoman after she reported a crime to    
OL,13,FGreater Manchester Police (GMP).       
OL,15,FAs a result, the Crown Prosecution     
OL,16,FService (CPS) brought charges against  
OL,17,Fthe 47-year-old.                       
OL,19,FAn IOPC spokeswoman said Rose's actions
OL,20,Fhad "absolutely no place in policing". 
